The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to colored points in the plane, which is a classic topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of range trees and dynamic programming suggests that the paper also involves data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DM). The consistent subset problem is a combinatorial optimization problem, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper presents algorithms that use geometric transformations and Voronoi diagrams, which are common tools in computational geometry and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
